EQUINE INFECTIOUS ANEMIA - GERMANY: (RHINELAND-PALATINATE)
**********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 8 Aug 2012
Source: Rhineland-Palatinate State Agency for Consumer and Health Protection press release [in German, trans. & summ. SZ, edited]
http://lua.rlp.de/einzelansicht/archive/2012/august/article/infektioese-anaemie-bei-pferden-rheinland-pfalz-erneut-betroffen/


A case of equine infectious anemia (EIA) has been confirmed in a 2-month-old foal from Rhineland-Palatinate. All equines from the holding and surrounding farms tested negative for the virus, including the mother of the foal.

Investigations are underway to establish how the foal became infected. It was born on the holding but had been transported earlier to a horse clinic in North Rhine-Westphalia twice for conditions that are not related to EIA.

Tracing of contact horses is under way.

--
Communicated by:
Sabine Zentis
