[EIA recurred in Germany in September 2006, after its absence since June 2002. The number of reported outbreaks (infected sites) since 2006, as reported to the OIE, was as follows:
2006 - 7; 2007 - 2; 2008 - 10; 2009 - 4; 2010 - 27; 2011 - 5.

The countrywide spread of EIA during 2010-2011, shared with other EU member countries, was attributed to introduction of infected horses from Romania. Results of the epidemiological investigation of the current outbreak are anticipated.

EIA is not zoonotic. For an updated review, see http://www.cfsph.iastate.edu/Factsheets/pdfs/equine_infectious_anemia.pdf. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1GBu.]
